import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of life expectancy over time?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    plt.scatter(data['fertility'], data['life_expect'])
    plt.title('What is the relationship between fertility and life expectancy?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Fertility')
    plt.ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.sort_values(by='pop', ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['country'], data['pop'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across countries?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot([data[data['cluster'] == i]['life_expect'].dropna() for i in range(6)], labels=[f'Cluster {i}' for i in range(6)])
    ax.set_xlabel('Cluster')
    ax.set_ylabel('Life Expectancy')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of life expectancy across clusters?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
